     <section class="post-27 page type-page status-publish hentry" id="post-27">
      <header>
       <h1 id="entry-title">
        Campus Administrative Manual
       </h1>
      </header>
      <p>
       The Campus Administrative Manual (CAM) is one of several policy manuals for the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. The CAM includes policies and procedures as well as links to additional information on unit websites.  As these documents are reviewed and updated, policies may be removed from the CAM and archived, including their corresponding policy number. This removal may be reflected by a gap in numbering in this manual.
      </p>
      <p>
       This on-line version of CAM is the most current. Web publishers are requested to link to policy pages instead of copying them to ensure that readers have the most current and up-to-date information available.
      </p>
      <p>
       Policies in the CAM are reviewed periodically by members of the CAM Committee.  Revisions for current policies and drafts of new policies are submitted for review by the committe members after approriate parties outside of the CAM Committee are consulted.
      </p>
      <p>
       Contact
       <a href="https://forms.illinois.edu/sec/9640159">
        Campus Administrative Manual staff
       </a>
       to provide feedback on the policies and CAM website.
      </p>
      <p>
       Additional policies can be found here:
       <a href="https://www.bot.uillinois.edu/governance/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
        Board of Trustees,
       </a>
       <a href="https://provost.illinois.edu/policies/provosts-communications/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
        Provost’s Communications,
       </a>
       <a href="http://studentcode.illinois.edu/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
        Student Code,
       </a>
       <a href="https://nessie.uihr.uillinois.edu/cf/policies/index.cfm?Item_ID=874&amp;rlink=374">
        NESSIE
       </a>
       , and
       <a href="https://www.obfs.uillinois.edu/bfpp/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
        OBFS Policies.
       </a>
      </p>
     </section>
    </main>
